## Waiver Policy Summary

All waivers must:
1. Have documented justification
2. Have assessed residual risk level
3. Be approved by the designated authority (see `references/gate-criteria-reference.md`)
4. Have an expiry date or closure condition
5. Have a monitoring plan for the accepted risk

## Completeness Checklist
- [ ] All waivers documented with full details
- [ ] Residual risk level assessed for each waiver
- [ ] Approved by designated authority
- [ ] Conditions and monitoring defined
